Ruth Adrineda wrote:
&gt; has anybody used [assert() in callbacks]?

I do. When I implement MockObjects (which I use for callbacks, amongst other
things), I usually make them extend from junit.framework.Assert. This gives
me access to all the various assert() methods.

I use assert() to enforce the contract imposed on the interface I&#39;m mocking.
If a method shouldn&#39;t take a null argument, I enforce it, and so on.

